data.summary: [PR Newswire] - STEVENSON, Md., Sept. 13, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The securities litigation law firm of Brower Piven, A Professional Corporation, has commenced an investigation into possible breaches of fiduciary duty and other violations of state law by the Board of Directors of Alteva, Inc. (NYSE MKT: ALTV) ("Alteva" or the "Company") relating to the proposed buyout of the Company by Momentum Telecom, Inc. ("Momentum Telecom"), in a transaction valued at approximately $28.7 million. Under the terms of the transaction, Alteva shareholders are anticipated to receive $4.70 in cash for each share of Alteva common stock held. The firm's investigation seeks to determine, among other things, whether the Company's Board of Directors failed to satisfy their duties to shareholders, including whether the Board adequately pursued alternatives to the acquisition and whether the Board obtained the best price possible for the Company's shares of common stock.
data.title: SHAREHOLDER ALERT: Brower Piven Commences An Investigation Into The Proposed Sale Of Alteva, Inc. And Encourages Investors To Contact The Firm For Additional Information
